items.name: Penguin Empire Mooks - Kenzen Robo Daimidaler (optimizer tests)
items.description:
MAE SHIPPO! IT'S a FRONT TAIL YOU DEVIANTS!

V2:

This time I tested the Prodigy optimizer, same dataset.

Prodigy LR=1 DR=.01 Dim=32 Alpha=16

Vs

AdamW LR=.0001 DR=.1 Dim=32 Alpha=16 Scale Weights Normals

vs

AdamW LR=.0001 DR=.1 Dim=32 Alpha=16

The result: Contrary to DAdaptAdam I got good results with Prodigy. In good conditions its behavior is similar to AdamW but with 15% more cost in training time. BUT! In less than ideal conditions when you are close to overbaking and using extra images to fight against bleedover, it performs significant better than AdamW with Scale Weights Normals and STUPIDLY BETTER than stock AdamW.

Conclusion: I would indeed recommend Prodigy for beginners as it is much more tolerant to overbaking and imbalances in the Learning rate vs repetitions vs dataset size. It also seems to help a bit with concept separation(but I tweaked everything as much as possible to maximize it in my sailor moon LORA.). The only issue is the extra required configuration it needs(It doesn't need to be adjusted). I added a pre configured template in my training guide if someone wants to check it out.

V1:

I needed a sacrifice to test the DAdaptAdam optimizer. Thus I trained two loras one as normal with

AdamW LR=.0001 DR=.1 Dim=32 Alpha=16

VS

DAdaptAdam LR= 1 DR=1 Dim=32 Alpha=16 25% slower

The result: The DAdaptAdam sucked so much ass compared to the normal recipe despite me using a default not fine tuned learning rate. Maybe it will get better with further experimentation but right now doesn't seem like it's its moment to shine. The fact it took longer makes it even worse.

Anyway...

As I didn't want to sacrifice a pretty lady for research purposes I used the Mooks of the penguin empire of the sadly underrated Daimidaler series a hilarious parody of the super robot genre.

It's refreshing when you agree with a series point of of view, the main characters of the second part of the series are extremely fucking annoying. The leader of prince was RIGHT!

Anyway what you are here for, humanoid penguins with front tails, got ok results with:

Positive: PenguinEmpireMook, standing, solo, masterpiece, best quality, highres, cloudy sky, <lora:PenguinEmpireMookV2:.7>

Negatives: lowres, bar censor, text, error, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, out of focus, censorship, censored, ((depth of field)), simple background, eyes, face, cape,

As they have no faces or definite hands, bad hands embeddings and face positive tags will likely make more damage than help. That's why I added the negatives too.

Clothing sets? I guess one guy uses a hat once.

For the dataset, well it is mostly screencaps so it is a no go, instead I will dump the training files and the other lora which I dare not publish(due to crapyness) if someone wants to review them.

For both anime and realistic, including long hair helps to keep her hair as long as it is the game.

items.name: Zuikaku (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Zuikaku from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 207 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.9], (1 - 0.6)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

ZuikakuKC, japanese clothes, twintails, white hair ribbon, red hakama short skirt, tasuki, black thighhighs, hair between eyes

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-single glove, partially fingerless gloves, yugake

items.description:
A LoRA trained on Sasha from animal crossing. It was trained on a custom model, but will absolutely work on any model that can produce anthro characters and probably any model trained on anime.

The trigger is 'sasha \(animal crossing\).' You may also have to specify hair and fur color.

If you have trouble producing the correct fur color, try using '(green body | blue body).' If you don't know what that does, it alternates each generation step between 'blue body' and 'green body,' producing a mix of the two colors. You can even use tag weights to fine tune further, as in '((blue body :1.2) | (green body :0.9))'

Hope you enjoy, you degenerates.

items.name: Bubble Drip
items.description:
Hi again and welcome to the Bubble world!

"Bubble Drip" is an experimental LORA that will create a very specific Bubblish-background dripping style. This version focus on orange/blue color scheme as it was created for testing purposes but turned out very flexible so, here it is.


Token is:Â Sy3Â (and nope, its not related to an artist or something, was to put a token trigger).

How to prompt
*****************
See the examples attached but:

1)Â Portrait/close up portrait/landscape/etc. of a [concept] in the style of Sy3
2)Â Cose up of a portrait/landscape/etc. of a [concept] in the style of Sy3
3)Â A [concept] in the style of Sy3


Of course you can decide to not put Sy3 but putting the Token will summon the effect easier. And you can always weight it if it's too much and so on.


Caution when usingÂ negative embeddingsÂ as easynegative and so on. I'd recommend to use it on a normal basis though.



Recommended values & models

*************************************

Didn't test on every model but AnyLora, RevAnimated and DreamShaper works.

For values if you use Token 0.7-01 are the values to go and when not using Token 0.8-1 are good values (and in certain cases it handles till 1.2).


Quick tip: Don't forget you can use "halfs" (0.85, 0.75, etc.).


This LORA is GOOD for:

***************************

- Poster/vectorized works

- Graphic design works.

- Portraits/landscapes

- Abstract/graffiti aesthetics in BG

- Subtle drip effects playing with strenght

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

Enjoy and don't forget you can support me and my pal in ourÂ PatreonÂ so we can keep creating more and better content.


David.

items.name: The thinker
items.description:
The Thinker is a bronze sculpture by Auguste Rodin, usually placed on a stone pedestal. The work depicts a nude male figure of heroic size sitting on a rock. The pose is one of deep thought and contemplation, and the statue is often used as an image to represent philosophy. The Thinker was initially named The Poet (French: Le PoÃ¨te), and was part of a large commission begun in 1880 for a doorway surround called The Gates of Hell. - wikipedia

The dataset contains data from below, from side and from behind, put them in prompt if you want. It is also possible to turn the character into statue by prompting [statue].

This lora can work well with certain character's lora, play with the weight a bit and see how it goes, the weights vary quite a bit depending on the loras. It was suggested to use [The thinker] at 1 weight, adjust the other character lora.

Go break some eggs, have fun!

outdoors, sky, day, cloud, tree, blue sky, no humans, grass, ground vehicle, scenery, torii, ultra-detailed, 8k, masterpiece, (no texts), no names, (volumetric lighting)

outdoors, sky, day, cloud, blue sky, no humans, night, moon, star (sky), night sky, scenery, starry sky, mountain, space, planet, earth (planet), above clouds, ultra-detailed, 8k, masterpiece, (no texts), no names, (volumetric lighting), (ambient light), realistic shadows

items.name: How To Train Your Dragon (People + Toothless)
items.description:
Making MyBreastHelper and MillenniumGirls I learned quite a bit about the things I've done wrong in the past.

I haven't seen any How To Train Your Dragon LoRA's other than Astrid, and as I've stated in the past, even though a single character LoRA is easier to train than a TI, I feel it's a waste. So here's a few more characters. Sorry I didn't add more Dragons, there's just not many usable shots of most of them. Even Toothless is a little wonky at times because there's not many good body shots, and he's the star. I was even able to include Gothi with some extra image padding.

Most images were pulled from the first movie but some of the supporting characters I had to supplement from the second. What's that mean? Some characters (mainly Snotlout, Fishlegs, and Tuffnut) will render older than they should with beards etc. Hiccup sometimes renders very "girlish" but that's the checkpoint used. Some checkpoints even try to make Gobber a woman.

items.name: Character Change - Vanguard Reverse (Link Joker)

The invasion of the Link Jokers is approaching. Enlist your characters to fight alongside them.

This LyCORIS is based off the original Link Joker clan from Cardfight!! Vanguard. It seems to perform very well to give that cyber aesthetic and forming the black-red ring that is iconic to the clan. Sometimes the ring will be in different colors, especially if you mix other LoRAs and LyCORIS.

Trigger words are: reverse, black ring
Additional words that might help: glowing, glowing eyes, android, robot,

Recommended weight between 0.6-1.0.
